=======================
| Python List Slicing |
=======================
👉 List Slicing is the process of extracting a portion of a list by specifying a start index, stop index, and optional step value.

list_name[start : stop : step]

start -> The starting index from where slicing begins (inclusive).  Included
stop -> The ending index where slicing stops (exclusive).   Excluded
step -> The interval between selected elements.

numbers = [10,20,30,40,50,60]
print(numbers[1:4])
O/P : [20, 30, 40]

print(numbers[0:3])
O/P : [10,20,30]

print(numbers[:4])
O/P : [10,20,30,40]

print(numbers[2:])
O/P : [30,40,50,60]

print(numbers[:])     # Whole List copy
O/P : [10,20,30,40,50,60]

print(numbers[0:6:2])
O/P : [10,30,50]

print(numbers[0:6:3])
O/P : [10,40]

print(numbers[-5:-2])  # Negative Slicing
O/P : [20,30,40]

print(numbers[::-1])  # Reverse List
O/P : [60,50,40,30,20,10]

print(numbers[::2])  # Every Second Element
O/P : [10,30,50]

print(numbers[::3])   # Every Third Element
O/P : [10,40]

print(numbers[::-2])  # Reverse Every Second Element
O/P : [60,40,20]


===============
| Quick Table |
===============
_______________________________________________
| Slice        | Output                       |
| ------------ | ---------------------------- |
| `list[:]`    | Entire list (copy)           |
| `list[1:4]`  | Index 1 to 3                 |
| `list[:4]`   | Start to index 3             |
| `list[3:]`   | Index 3 to end               |
| `list[::2]`  | Every second element         |
| `list[::-1]` | Reverse list                 |
| `list[-3:]`  | Last three elements          |
| `list[:-1]`  | All except last              |
| `list[::-2]` | Reverse every second element |
